<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport"
          content="width=device-width, user-scalable=no, initial-scale=1.0, maximum-scale=1.0, minimum-scale=1.0">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="ie=edge">
    <style>
        * {
            font-family: monospace;
        }

        body {
            margin: 40px;
        }

        .code {
            background-color: #f2f2f2;
            border-radius: 2px;
            padding: 4px 8px;
            display: inline-block;
        }

        div, span, li {
            font-size: 1.2rem;
        }

        #js {
            background-color: #F7E018;
            font-family: sans-serif;
            font-size: 1.6rem;
            padding: 1.2rem 0.3rem 0.2rem 0.8rem;
        }

        li {
            margin: 8px 0;
        }

        ul {
            margin: 24px 0;
        }

    </style>
    <title>ID Generator</title>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>A tiny id generator coded with <span id="js">JS</span></h1>
    <div>Creates lovely ids for your app.</div>

    <div>There are two API options (both POST requests):</div>
    <ul>
        <li><span class="code">localhost:5050/id?limit=&lt;number&gt;</span>: Generates an id with the digits equal to limit. Default limit is 8.</li>
        <li><span class="code">localhost:5050/valid?id=&lt;id&gt;</span>: Returns a boolean value base on the validation of the given id.</li>
        <li><span class="code">localhost:5050/docs</span>: Gets an HTML page with documentation.</li>
    </ul>

